org.orgName: District Court of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory

body.p: In the matter of the application of C.F. Reed for Writ of Habeas Corpus
In the District Court of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory, holding Terms at Seattle, King County, Wash. Terr.
In the matter of he application of No.5931 C.F. Reed Petition for a Writ. For a Writ of Habeas Corpus.
To the Hon. Richard A. Jones, Chief Justice of the Supreme Court and the sole Presiding Judge of the said District Court:

Your petitioner, C.F. Reed, states that he is unlawfully imprisoned, detained, confined and restrained of his liberty by William Cochrane, Sheriff of the County of King in Washington Territory, at the County Jail in the said City of Seattle in said County.
That the said imprisonment, detention, confinement and restraint are illegal.

That the cause and pretence of said restraint, imprisonment, confinement and detention is a paper writing purporting to be commitment from N. Soderberg, Justice of the Peace for Seattle, Precinct, King County, Washington Territory.

That the illegality of said restraint, imprisonment, detention and confinement is this: That the said paper writing is not a commitment in this: That it does not show that said Defendant has been convicted of any offence, or that the Court issuing said paper writing had any jurisdiction to commit said Defendant: and that paper writing is not a commitment, but is void and no affect whatever: and that said Sheriff has no right or authority to detain said Petitioner thereon.
That a copy of said paper writing, alleged to be a commitment, is filed herewith as part hereof, and marked "Exhibit A".
Wherefore, your Petitioner prays that a writ of Habeas Corpus directed to said Sheriff may issue in this behalf, and that your
Petitioner may be forthwith brought before your Honor to do, submit for and receive what the law may require.
Territory of Washington, County of King } ss.
C.F. Reed, your Affiant, says: I am the Petitioner above named. That I have read the foregoing Petition, and know its contents, and that the same is true.
Subscribed and sworn to before me this 27th day of April, 1888. Notary Public in and for Washington Territory.
